               <extent> 2p</extent>
               <note type="summary" anchored="true">This document is a letter written from J. Pike &amp; Company to Doctor A. King &amp; Company dated March 16, 1836. The letter shows a listing of medicines ordered by Doctor A. King &amp; Company from J. Pike &amp; Company. The medicines are arriving late because of delays due to a canal being closed. Some of the medicines listed are herbs and seasonings used to create medicines. The letter is concluded by giving a recipe for wine bitter using some of the medicines named in the letter.</note>
